						<summary>Sefer otsar ha-kavod.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="1r" to="185v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer otsar ha-kavod</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר אוצר הכבוד </title>
							<note>
								<p>The text is not preceded be either introduction or verses. There is no table of contents or division into numbered paragraphs.</p>
								<p>The text itself is often corrupt.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. the contents of Or 62, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">742</ref>, II.</filiation>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">נשלם ספר הנקרא אוצר הכבוד בשנת <date calendar="Hebrew">הקס"א</date> ביום ב' בכ"ה ימים לחודש מרחשון למניין שאנו רגילים [?ל]מ[?נ]ות פה בקהל <name type="place">נקופולי</name>, וכתבתיו לכבוד הרב רבנא <name type="person" role="patron">ר' שמעון</name> והשם יזכנו להגות בו הוא ובניו ובני בנ[?י]ו עד סוף כל הדורות ויבורך בברכה שניתנה לישראל בלי תנאי אמן ואמן נ[?צח] סלה

<locus n="185v"/>
							</colophon>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/24783259">Abulafia, Todros ben Joseph, ha-Levi, approximately 1220-1298</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/24783259"> 	אבולעפיה, טודרוס בן יוסף, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Todros_Abulafia_1807"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the early 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>185 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>220</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>160</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>185 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 12 leaves each, marked by catchwords at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
									<p>2 leaves missing after folio 10, and 1 leaf after folios 21 and 31 respectively.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="28" writtenLines="28">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Decorated catchwords, folio 103v, 171v.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Byzantine (Greek) semi-cursive script of the early 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Eliyahu</name>: his name marked off on folio 170v.</summary>
